Freudenthal, Respondent, v. Schenkewitz, Appellant. (Common Pleas of New York City and County, General Term. December 19, 1889.) Appeal from fifth district court.

Argued before Van Hoesen, P. J,, and Bookstaver, J.

H. C. Kudlich, for appellant. Langbein Bros. & Langbein, for respondent.

No opinion. Ordered that the judgment be affirmed, with costs.
